data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** The test compiled and ran successfully:

```csharp
Span<nint> nints = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> nuints = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

Both work as expected. On this 64-bit system, `sizeof(nint)` is 8 bytes. This feature is available since C# 9 / .NET 5, when `nint`/`nuint` were introduced as first-class unmanaged types (which is the requirement for `stackalloc`).
